The paper discusses sponsored search auctions, which are a subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The focus on fast and scalable techniques suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the use of bidding strategies and optimization techniques suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
